Independent Director of NSEIT, the first CERT CEO and the first National Cybersecurity Coordinator, the person who should be accountable for responding to and taking action on breaches at NSEIT.</p><p>The only thing he could say to the operator was: &ldquo;Do you know who I am?&rdquo;, &ldquo;Oh, it&rsquo;s you damn hackers&rdquo;, etc. The company was notified through various channels with evidence attached. Thereafter, NSEIT chose to remain silent, not to respond, not to announce the data breach. This calls into question the competence of people like Dr. Gulshan Rai, who should have vast experience in cyber security, and they did not even care to request a list of all the leaked files to verify it and take remedial measures to deal with the breach.
